Otherwise we'd add duplicate intervals.

2. No Overlap
if (ans.empty() || ans.back()[1] < interval[0])
What does this mean?
ans.back()[1] = ending point of the last merged interval.
interval[0] = starting point of current interval.
If:
lastEnd < currentStart
then there is a gap between them.
So they cannot overlap.



